---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Seguin Neighborhoods | Cody Posey Real Estate"
  description="Explore Seguin, TX neighborhoods by area and price range. From historic downtown to new construction communities — find the right fit for your lifestyle."
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="seg-hero">
      <div class="seg-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="seg-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/seguin/">Seguin</a> <span>/</span> <span>Neighborhoods</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Seguin <span style="color:#FF1616;">Neighborhoods</span></h1>
        <p>Find the area that fits your lifestyle and budget</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="seg-page-intro seg-page-intro--centered">Seguin offers a range of neighborhoods — from established family communities and historic downtown living to newer construction and large-lot properties along the Guadalupe River. Here is how the city breaks down.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 1.5rem auto 0; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.8; text-align: center;">Located about 35 miles east of San Antonio along I-10, Seguin has emerged as one of the most affordable alternatives to the San Antonio metro while still offering strong community character and convenient access to employment centers. The city is experiencing steady growth driven by nearby manufacturing, including the Tesla Gigafactory and Caterpillar operations, as well as its proximity to Randolph Air Force Base. Seguin blends small-town Texas charm with practical value — making it attractive to first-time buyers, military families, investors, and anyone looking for more home and land for their dollar compared to New Braunfels or San Antonio.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Neighborhoods -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Seguin <span class="accent">Neighborhoods</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-nob-hill.png" alt="Nob Hill homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>Nob Hill</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$250K - $350K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Primarily anchored by Nob Hill Condominiums, this established community offers a budget-friendly entry into homeownership in Seguin. The neighborhood features a tranquil atmosphere with mature trees and calmer streets, plus a community pool and clubhouse. Especially appealing to first-time buyers and downsizers, Nob Hill is served by Seguin ISD. The condominiums provide a low-maintenance lifestyle with HOA-managed exteriors and common areas. Units typically feature two to three bedrooms with updated interiors, and the community's pricing makes it one of the most accessible homeownership opportunities in Guadalupe County.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-mill-creek.png" alt="Village of Mill Creek homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>Village of Mill Creek</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$200K - $320K</span>
          </div>
          <p>A quiet, family-friendly neighborhood with a close-knit vibe and larger lots than many surrounding communities. Village of Mill Creek offers easy access to New Braunfels, Randolph AFB, the Tesla Gigafactory, the Guadalupe River, and Lake McQueeney. Some sections have no HOA, and homes include a mix of one and two-story layouts. Served by Seguin ISD. The neighborhood draws families and military personnel who appreciate the generous lot sizes and the flexibility that comes with no-HOA sections. Homes here typically feature traditional Texas ranch-style construction with brick and stone exteriors, attached garages, and covered patios. The central location between San Antonio and New Braunfels makes Mill Creek a practical choice for dual-income households with different commutes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-cordova-crossing.png" alt="Cordova Crossing homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>Cordova Crossing</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$280K - $400K</span>
          </div>
          <p>A modern, family-friendly community with a relaxed neighborly atmosphere, wide streets, and sidewalks. Cordova Crossing features a playground, private dog park, and trails throughout the neighborhood. Homes showcase contemporary designs with open layouts, smart home technology, and energy-efficient construction. Served by Seguin ISD. As one of the newer developments in Seguin, Cordova Crossing appeals to buyers who want the look and feel of a master-planned community at a fraction of what similar neighborhoods cost closer to San Antonio. Builders in this community offer a range of floor plans from three-bedroom starter homes to five-bedroom executive layouts with three-car garages. The neighborhood's HOA maintains common areas and enforces design standards to preserve property values.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-downtown.png" alt="Downtown Seguin homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>Downtown Seguin</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$150K - $300K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Charming, walkable living in the heart of the city with access to boutiques, cafes, and restaurants along Main Street. Properties in the historic district include Victorian-era houses, bungalows, and mid-century ranches — each with its own character. Downtown Seguin is steeped in rich Texas history and is ideal for buyers who value character and convenience. Many of the homes in this area qualify for historic preservation tax incentives, and renovation projects are common. The downtown core has seen a resurgence in recent years with new restaurants, a growing arts scene, and community events centered around the historic courthouse square. This is also a strong area for real estate investors interested in rental properties or short-term vacation homes.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-country-club.png" alt="Country Club Estates homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>Country Club Estates</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$250K - $450K</span>
          </div>
          <p>Located near Seguin Country Club, this neighborhood offers an "open vista community" feel with pool and clubhouse amenities. An Architectural Review Committee maintains neighborhood standards, ensuring a well-kept and cohesive streetscape. Country Club Estates is a solid choice for buyers seeking an established neighborhood with recreational access. Served by Seguin ISD. Homes in Country Club Estates tend to be mid-size to larger single-family residences with brick or stone exteriors, manicured yards, and covered porches. The neighborhood draws move-up buyers and empty nesters who want a well-maintained environment with easy access to golf and social amenities. The Architectural Review Committee helps keep the neighborhood looking sharp and protects long-term property values.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="seg-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/seg-river-oaks.png" alt="River Oaks homes" class="seg-area__img" loading="lazy" />
          <div class="seg-area__header">
            <h3>River Oaks</h3>
            <span class="seg-area__price">$300K - $500K</span>
          </div>
          <p>A quiet, family-friendly neighborhood where some homes have waterfront access to Lake Seguin and the Guadalupe River, including boat docks. River Oaks features a diverse mix of properties — from vintage bungalows and postwar mid-century ranches to newer modern farmhouse and contemporary builds. A great option for buyers who want variety, water access, and a relaxed pace close to town. Waterfront lots in River Oaks command a premium, but interior lots remain competitively priced compared to similar water-adjacent neighborhoods in New Braunfels. The area is popular with buyers who enjoy fishing, kayaking, and outdoor recreation. Homes range from modest two-bedroom cottages to spacious four-bedroom properties with upgraded kitchens and outdoor entertaining areas overlooking the water.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- School District -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>School <span class="accent">District</span></h2>
          <p>Seguin's schools serve a growing and diverse community</p>
        </div>
        <div class="seg-schools__grid">
          <a href="https://www.seguin.k12.tx.us" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="seg-schools__card">
            <h3>Seguin ISD</h3>
            <p>Seguin ISD serves the city and surrounding areas with a focus on college readiness, career training, and community involvement. The district operates multiple campuses from pre-K through high school.</p>
            <span class="seg-schools__link">Visit Seguin ISD Website →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Need Help <span class="accent">Narrowing It Down</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I can walk you through the differences between Seguin neighborhoods and help you focus your search on areas that match your priorities.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Get Help Choosing a Neighborhood</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/porch-view.png" />

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Seguin Neighborhoods</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the most affordable neighborhood in Seguin?</summary>
          <p>Downtown Seguin offers some of the most affordable housing in the area, with properties starting around $150K. These include historic bungalows, mid-century ranches, and Victorian-era homes with character and walkability to local shops and restaurants. Nob Hill is another budget-friendly option with condominiums starting in the $250K range that include community amenities like a pool and clubhouse. Both areas provide solid entry points for first-time buyers looking to build equity in a growing market.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which Seguin neighborhoods are best for families with children?</summary>
          <p>Cordova Crossing and Village of Mill Creek are two of the strongest family-oriented neighborhoods in Seguin. Cordova Crossing is a newer development with wide sidewalks, a playground, dog park, and walking trails — plus modern homes with energy-efficient construction. Village of Mill Creek offers larger lots and a close-knit community feel with easy access to schools and recreation. Both neighborhoods are served by Seguin ISD and offer a safe, welcoming environment for families.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Is Seguin a good place to invest in real estate?</summary>
          <p>Seguin is increasingly attractive to real estate investors due to its affordability relative to San Antonio and New Braunfels, combined with strong growth drivers like the Tesla Gigafactory and Caterpillar operations nearby. Rental demand is growing as more workers relocate to the area, and home values have appreciated steadily. Downtown Seguin and River Oaks are particularly popular with investors looking at long-term rentals or short-term vacation properties near the Guadalupe River.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the most affordable neighborhood in Seguin?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Downtown Seguin offers some of the most affordable housing in the area, with properties starting around $150K. These include historic bungalows, mid-century ranches, and Victorian-era homes with character and walkability to local shops and restaurants. Nob Hill is another budget-friendly option with condominiums starting in the $250K range that include community amenities like a pool and clubhouse."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which Seguin neighborhoods are best for families with children?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Cordova Crossing and Village of Mill Creek are two of the strongest family-oriented neighborhoods in Seguin. Cordova Crossing is a newer development with wide sidewalks, a playground, dog park, and walking trails. Village of Mill Creek offers larger lots and a close-knit community feel with easy access to schools and recreation. Both neighborhoods are served by Seguin ISD."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Is Seguin a good place to invest in real estate?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Seguin is increasingly attractive to real estate investors due to its affordability relative to San Antonio and New Braunfels, combined with strong growth drivers like the Tesla Gigafactory and Caterpillar operations nearby. Rental demand is growing as more workers relocate to the area, and home values have appreciated steadily."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I need help narrowing down Seguin neighborhoods..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .seg-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/home-nb-ranch.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .seg-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .seg-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .seg-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .seg-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .seg-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .seg-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Neighborhood Cards */
  .seg-area {
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .seg-area__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .seg-area__header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: space-between;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    gap: 0.5rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .seg-area__header h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: 1.5rem;
  }

  .seg-area__price {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #FF1616;
    background: rgba(255,22,22,0.08);
    padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .seg-area p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Schools */
  .seg-schools__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .seg-schools__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .seg-schools__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .seg-schools__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .seg-schools__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .seg-schools__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .seg-schools__link {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }
</style>
